pounds of cocaine into switzerland was convicted and sentenced to 
eight years in prison for breaking narcotics laws 
a geneva jury court friday sentenced three brazilian 
codefendants to jail terms of up to 15 years for membership in a 
ring smuggling the drug from brazil to milan italy 
the rev lino christ a roman catholic parish priest in rio de 
janeiro admitted he frequently traveled to geneva to raise funds 
for charity 
but a codefendant implicated him in the ring where couriers 
were rewarded with 10000 a trip christ shared an apartment with 
a mistress in rios plush copacabana district the court was told 
all brazilian priests have a little business on the side 
christ testified in court but he did not elaborate 
he was arrested in december after geneva airport customs 
officials seized cocaine with a street value of 18 million hidden 
under a false bottom of his suitcase 
