<TEXT>
justice sandra day oconnor the first woman 
on the supreme court is recovering from surgery for breast cancer 
and expects to return to work in 10 days 
oconnor 58 underwent surgery friday at georgetown university 
hospital but few details on the procedure or followup treatment 
were provided 
i underwent surgery for breast cancer it was found to exist 
in a very early form and stage oconnor said in a statement 
released by supreme court spokeswoman toni house the prognosis 
is for total recovery i do not anticipate missing any oral 
arguments oconnor said 
the court is on a twoweek recess and returns to hear arguments 
oct 31 the justices also will meet in private conference oct 28 
but it was not known whether oconnor will attend 
dr robert s siegel assistant professor of medicine and 
director of a cancer treatment unit at george washington university 
hospital said oconnors plan for a quick return to the bench 
would be a remarkably fast recovery and may be good news for 
her prognosis 
he said the speed also may indicate the cancer was caught at a 
very early time and there is no indication it has spread to other 
organs in the body siegel is not involved in oconnors case 
it was not disclosed whether oconnors surgery was for removal 
of a lump or the entire breast there also were no details on 
whether the justice will receive any form of continuing treatment 
and when the cancer was discovered 
siegel said that typically when breast cancer is detected at a 
very early stage the patient can choose to have either a 
lumpectomy in which only the tumor is removed from the breast or 
a modified radical mastectomy in which the entire breast is 
removed 
either procedure usually involves removal of the lymph glands 
under the arm 
for a lumpectomy patients generally are released from the 
hospital in three to four days siegel said but return in two 
weeks to start radiation therapy 
the radiation usually is given once a day four to five days a 
week for four to six weeks 
for most patients this is a difficult period because the 
radiation causes fatigue 
it would be difficult to maintain a full schedule while 
receiving radiation said siegel but he noted that some patients 
handle it much more easily than others 
patients receiving a modified radical mastectomy do not require 
radiation therapy and usually return to work within two to three 
weeks 
oconnors operation came just a year after first lady nancy 
reagan underwent surgery to remove her left breast after laboratory 
tests revealed a quarterinch cancerous lesion 
mrs reagan then 66 recovered quickly from the oct 17 1987 
surgery a modified radical mastectomy 
oconnors health as far as is publicly known has been good 
she underwent an appendectomy in march and was soon back at work 
supreme court justices generally jealously guard the details of 
their health 
in 1986 the associated press inquired about a tremor a 
nodding motion of oconnors head that has been apparent to court 
watchers for years at times the justice will rest her chin on her 
hands during the courts public oral argument sessions 
oconnor sent back this reply through the courts public 
information office i was unaware of such a tendency as for 
resting her chin on her hands she said it is an old and perhaps 
unfortunate habit 
oconnors appointment to be a justice by president reagan in 
1981 ended 191 years of male exclusivity on the high court 
a political and judicial conservative she has been a champion 
of states rights and enhanced police power 
but while she generally sides with the conservative wing of the 
court anchored by chief justice william h rehnquist she has cast 
important moderate votes in such areas as sex discrimination and 
affirmative action 
she was a virtual unknown on the national scene when reagan 
picked her to replace potter stewart who had retired 
oconnor served as an arizona state judge and before that was a 
member of that states legislature 
</TEXT>
