<TEXT>
william j campbell a us 
district judge who prosecuted gangster al capone and was the 
longesttenured federal judge in the united states died wednesday 
of complications from surgery he was 83 
campbell was one of the prosecutors who got the notorious 
chicago hoodlum convicted on taxevasion charges capone died in 
prison in 1947 
campbell appointed to the federal bench in 1940 by president 
franklin d roosevelt rose to become chief judge in illinois 
northern district and twice declined a seat on the 7th us circuit 
court of appeals 
he retired in 1970 but continued to hear federal cases in 
