for maritime research which he said has been slashed 
gray whales were hunted to near extinction by the 1920s when 
their numbers dipped to below 1000 while their skins were used for 
buggy whips and corsets and their teeth fashioned into ivory 
jewelry 
environmentalists now estimate their population at about 20000 
