speeches with an eye toward getting a particular few seconds on the 
news but quayle said that isnt all bad 
what you have right now is you have to get a story across and 
the temptation is to say ok weve got a message today we want to 
get across on our own terms and nobody elses quayle said 
thats a pretty good strategy he said you cant fault 
the strategy 
the people by and large know a lot about all four of us 
he said its more oriented to oneliners but you know 
oneliners say a lot 
lets not minimize the importance of oneliners 
