<TEXT>
rep pat swindall is attempting to beat an 
election day deadline with his oneman rushtojustice defense in 
a federal perjury trial that will climax one of the countrys most 
bitter congressional elections 
if everything goes as expected the twoterm republican 
congressman will deliver his opening argument in us district 
court on monday just one week after his indictment was handed up 
and just 15 days before the nov 8 election 
swindall a lawyer is representing himself in the perjury case 
and hopes a quick acquittal will bring victory at the polls 
he has admitted to a mistake in judgment in negotiating an 
850000 loan last year with an undercover agent posing as a 
financier but denies criminal wrongdoing eventually swindall 
accepted a 150000 check from a middleman then returned it 
uncashed 
the 10 perjury charges brought against swindall stem from his 
testimony before a grand jury in february among other things 
swindall testified he could not recall any mention of drug money 
tapes of the meetings have the agent saying the loan money was 
probably drugrelated 
swindall is facing the same challenger he did in 1986 in his bid 
for a third term in the house he calls it a race between a 
dukakis liberal and a bush conservative 
voters in the suburbs east of atlanta will choose between 
swindall and democrat ben jones a onetime dukes of hazzard tv 
star who has had to answer repeated questions from swindall about 
his admitted bout with alcoholism 
though swindall demanded the speedy trial to obtain a verdict 
before the election he has stressed his disadvantage in manpower 
and time to prepare for the trial saying he will just have to rely 
on the ol innocent defense 
in fact he will have more going for him said lawyer guy davis 
a former policeman and prosecutor who was the republican nominee 
for governor in 1986 davis has been a critic of swindall but 
expressed admiration for his tactics in the case 
davis said he has seen both laymen and lawyers successfully 
defend themselves 
many defendants found that there was an advantage in that the 
jury was continously being exposed to the defendant himself while 
he conducts the trial he said 
if swindall is a good courtroom performer he said he will be 
able to impress his case on the jurors from the time the trial 
starts and not just from the time he takes the witness stand 
but robert fierer who has handled a string of highprofile 
criminal cases and represents another defendant in the 
moneylaundering probe said that while swindall may get the 
underdogs sympathy from the jury he is sacrificing some 
potentially important options in rushing to trial 
he really has given up investigative time the time to go out 
and find witnesses to get prepared on witnesses and that sort of 
thing fierer said davis however noted that swindall has had 
access to transcripts of his meetings with the undercover agent for 
some time so hes probably no doubt wellprepared to go to 
trial and i think probably it is a wise thing for him to do 
and davis said some pretrial skirmishing over what can be used 
in court and demands for information are not as crucial to swindall 
because in this case the facts are fairly simple 
if the trial starts monday swindall also gives up time for 
pretrial hearings that could have helped his defense especially 
on his claims that us attorney robert barr also a republican is 
promoting his career at swindalls expense 
us district judge robert vining ruled that swindall may not 
present those claims to the jury without conducting a pretrial 
hearing on whether barr could be subpoenaed swindall hasnt 
officially told the judge whether he wants the hearing but he has 
indicated he will not permit a delay in the trial 
it will be up to the jury to decide whether swindall can 
reconcile the tapes of his meetings with the undercover agent with 
his later grand jury testimony 
