here is the text of the democratic response to 
president reagans weekly radio address saturday from senate 
majority leader robert c byrd of west virginia 
in less than three weeks the american people will elect a new 
president it may be the most important election of this century 
on the surface this election has been a series of negative tv 
ads quicky polls and instant experts the ads the polls and the 
experts seem to be driving the process 
most americans are unhappy with what they are seeing on their 
televisions we are a big people and we want a wide view of whats 
at stake in this election everything important to the american 
people cannot be reduced to a sevensecond sound bite 
the ads on television arent going to tell you much of anything 
a little music some flag waving and then poof the ad is over 
its time to look beneath the surface and start asking the 
important questions 
we need a president who tends to the nations business who has 
a sense of the future 
we need a president who has a plan for making the trade deficit 
a trade surplus who is willing to make a real commitment to ending 
the policy of borrow and debt that has put us into a sea of red ink 
we need a president who wants to keep america strong and who 
knows that economic power and military strength go hand in hand we 
need a president who believes in america so much that he is not 
afraid to tell us we have problems that need fixing 
we need a president who ways the same thing in public that he 
says in private and who wont make secret deals with the ayatollah 
two years ago the american people put the democrats back in 
charge of the senate we won in 1986 because we told the american 
people we would make a difference in their lives 
our agenda was clear and exact check and balance a white house 
that seemed to have lost its way we delivered despite two years of 
confrontation 
when the american people asked for a clean water bill we 
delivered despite a white house that said no 
when american workers wanted a new trade bill and jobs for 
americans we delivered despite a white house that said no 
when the american people demanded fairness on plant closing we 
delivered despite a white house that said no 
when the american people demanded an end to the slash and 
burn education policy of the white house it was the congress 
that said yes 
so who is in the mainstream of american politics a look at the 
record of the democratic congress will answer that question 
this congress has tried to be a family congress we have 
tackled the problems that people talk about when they sit around 
the kitchen table 
for our senior citizens we have expanded medicare to include 
catastrophic health insurance 
for twopaycheck families we fought for parental leave and 
child care bills only to run into a white house filibuster 
for millions of working men and women we fought for an increase 
in the minimum wage despite white house opposition 
for our nations security we fought against waste and fraud in 
the pentagon 
as majority leader of the senate democrats i take pride in the 
work of the 100th congress we have done our duty we have 
addressed your concerns we have listened to the people 
harry truman once said that polls are like sleeping pills 
designed to lull voters into sleeping on election day 
dont let the polls lull you to sleep dont let the political 
hucksters pick the next president 
look beneath the surface look to the record vote for the 
future remember that america is always at its best when we face 
our problems and never stand still 
thank you and god bless you 
</TEXT>
