at the request of nationalist activists he said a nationalist 
monument in vilnius that was destroyed under soviet dictator josef 
stalin will be rebuilt 
victims of stalins repressions will be rehabilitated and they 
or their survivors compensated he said and all the blank 
spots in lithuanias history will be cleared up 
the soviet union took control of the independent baltic states 
in 1940 under a secret pact with nazi germany activists in all 
three republics are demanding that authorities renounce the pact 
in draft resolutions up for a vote over at the meeting the 
lithuanian group said the 1940 takeover was an unlawful 
occupation and that the republic reserves its right to withdraw 
from the soviet union 
groups in estonia and latvia have adopted similar resolutions 
but in several respects the lithuanian measures are more radical 
in its draft resolutions the movement says defense and foreign 
policy should be handled jointly by the republic and the kremlin 
it says lithuanians should have the right to perform compulsory 
military service in their republic and to set up their own 
diplomatic missions abroad 
the movement was formed in june and claims 180000 supporters 
among the republics 36 million people 
