swing to bush after the presidential debate last week then missed 
some shifting back to dukakis on monday she noted that bush 
received wide publicity as the debate winner 
other pollsters shared her view noting that dukakis surged 
after the democratic convention last summer and bush after the 
republican convention but settled back as the publicity wore off 
their hypothesis when voters dont have strong opinions they 
are more likely to be influenced by events albeit momentarily 
polling immediately after momentous events catches people in 
the process of making up their minds what you see are these 
distortions said kohut the gallup president he likened it to a 
runners pulse after a race its an accurate reading but you 
cant generalize a lot from it 
kohut and others said such skittishness in the electorate 
magnifies the methodological differences in polls whether or not 
they urge undecided voters to make a choice for example and can 
help skew results 
